 <div class="section join" id="join">
   <div class="container">
     <div class="row">
       <h2 class="main-heading">Participate to UCN Study</h2>
       <h5>by contributing data on your online activities and network performance</h5>
     </div>
     <div class="row">
       <a class="button" href="hostviewinstaller.exe">
         HostView for Windows
       </a>
       <a class="button" href="hostview.apk">
         HostView for Android
       </a>
     </div>
     <div class="row">
       <p class="join-section-description">
         Hostview is a small data collection tool that we have developed for the UCN study. It runs on your device on the background and collects data on your activities (device and screen states, running applications, foreground window, visited URLs, presence of mouse, keyboard, audio or video events) and raw system performance data (cpu, memory, network traffic). Few times a day, it will ask you to indicate your current activity and rate the performance of your system. The tool is designed to consume little system resources and data uploads are scheduled only when there is little other traffic. You can pause the data collection at anytime. You can also visualize your data on our website in order to get more insight into your online activities, content consumption and delivery performance. We hope you will install Hostview at least for three months, after which it will prompt you to uninstall (unless you decide to keep running it!).
       </p>
     </div>
